- 1.B.

When $0<x<\frac{\pi}{2}$,
$$
\begin{array}{l}
f(x)=\left(\cot x+\frac{1}{\sin x}\right)^{2}=\left(\frac{1+\cos x}{\sin x}\right)^{2} \\
=\left(\frac{2 \cos ^{2} \frac{x}{2}}{2 \sin \frac{x}{2} \cdot \cos \frac{x}{2}}\right)^{2}=\cot ^{2} \frac{x}{2} \in(1,+\infty) ;
\end{array}
$$

When $-\frac{\pi}{2}<x<0$,
$$
\begin{array}{l}
f(x)=\left(-\cot x+\frac{1}{\sin x}\right)^{2}=\left(\frac{-\cos x+1}{\sin x}\right)^{2} \\
=\tan ^{2} \frac{x}{2} \in(0,1) .
\end{array}
$$

Therefore, the range of $f(x)$ is $\mathbf{R}_{+} \mid\{1\}$.

